<DOC><DOCNO> AP881207-0085 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-07-88 0908EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-BRF--Kitty'sBook     12-07 0145</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Kitty's Book,0148</SECOND><HEAD>Governor's Wife Reportedly Picks Publisher</HEAD><DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Kitty Dukakis, wife of Gov. Michael Dukakis, plansto write a book about her experiences on the campaign trail, TheBoston Globe reported today.   The Globe said unidentified sources reported that Mrs. Dukakischose Simon andamp; Shuster of New York to publish the book.   Mrs. Dukakis on Tuesday refused to say whether she had reached anagreement with a publisher or to give any details about the project.d withthe governor in his unsuccessfulbid for the presidency.   Two top editors at Simon andamp; Shuster _ Executive Editor AliceMayhew and Editor in Chief Mitchell Korda _ will work on themanuscript, the newspaper said.   The Globe said its sources did not know whether Mrs. Dukakis willuse a ghostwriter or how much she will be paid.</TEXT></DOC>